[Map:
<<http://www.cnn.com/SPECIALS/1999/ocalan/stories/turkey.judiciary/link.turkey.m>http://www.cnn.com/SPECIALS/1999/ocalan/stories/turkey.judiciary/link.turkey.m
ap.jpg>]
[Quarantine of children bitten by ticks or closure of the zoo to school
children in an area where the CCHF virus has not been shown to be present does
not seem justified -- Ankara is a long way from the Black Sea, where the woman
was bitten. Even where the virus is present, people not in direct, physical
contact with animals infected with CCHF virus are not at risk of becoming
infected themselves. People become infected through the bite of infected
ticks or through direct exposure to bodily fluids of infected animals or
humans.- Mod.TMY/JW]
